      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 42
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This powerplant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver 333 hp with a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox offers tactile, short-throw shifts, sending power through a GKN-sourced variable M differential lock. This example is mechanically robust, with the critical rear subframe reinforcement already completed and a top-end refresh addressing the VANOS solenoid and seals. The chassis remains taut, benefitting from refreshed control arm bushings and a precise steering rack that provides exceptional feedback. While the exterior and interior show minor honest wear consistent with a well-loved driver, the engine\u2019s compression is within factory spec and the rod bearings have been proactively serviced. This is a high-performance machine optimized for mechanical longevity and analog engagement.",
      "price": 34500.0,
